  "title": "numericSelector cssClasses option for root applies to a parent div as well as the child <select>",
  "body": "```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.numericSelector({\r\n        container: '#numericSelector',\r\n        attributeName: 'thing.id',\r\n        options: [{label: 'name of thing', value: 1}],\r\n        cssClasses: {\r\n            root: 'form-control'\r\n        }\r\n    })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\noutputs the following HTML:\r\n```html\r\n<div>\r\n    <div class=\"ais-root ais-numeric-selector form-control\">\r\n        <div class=\"ais-body\">\r\n            <select class=\"ais-numeric-selector form-control\">\r\n                <option class=\"ais-numeric-selector--item\" value=\"1\">name of thing</option>\r\n            </select>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAccording to the documentation, it should only be applied to the select element. This is problematic in this scenario because I am using with bootstrap and it is making the output undesirable",
